Package FPP.LinearOptimization.Model.benders

Class Problem

  • java.lang.Object
    • FPP.LinearOptimization.Model.benders.Problem
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MasterProblem, SubProblem
    public class Problem
extends java.lang.Object
    This represents the problem in form of a simplex tableau.
    Functions, coefficients and the objective function values are saved separately,
    so you always can generate a simplex tableau of the current problem.
    Author:
    Stefan

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      Problem​(java.lang.Double[][] simplexTableau)
      Initializes a problem by a given simplex tableau.

      Tableau needs to be given in this way:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d, 0d, 200d}, restriction 1
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 0d, 50d}, restriction 2
      {0d, 0d, 1d, 0d, 80d}, restriction 3
      {0d, 0d, 3d, 10d, 500d}} function

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void addRestriction​(java.lang.Double[] coefficients, java.lang.Double b)
      This adds a restriction to the problem.

      example restriction:
      {1d, 2d, 0d, 0d}
      java.lang.Double[] getB()
      Returns the object function values of the method restrictions.

      example restrictions:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d, 0d},
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 0d},
      {0d, 0d, 1d, 0d}}

      Marked values of restrictions are returned this way:
      {0d, 0d, 0d}
      java.lang.Double[][] getCoefficients()
      This returns all coefficients of the problem restrictions.

      example coefficients:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d},
      {1d, 0d, 0d},
      {0d, 0d, 1d}}

      See difference to getRestrictions()!
      java.lang.Double[] getFunction()
      Returns the function of the current problem.

      example tableau:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d, 0d, 200d}, restriction 1
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 0d, 50d}, restriction 2
      {0d, 0d, 1d, 0d, 80d}, restriction 3
      {0d, 0d, 3d, 10d, 500d}} function

      In this case only the function line is returned:
      {0d, 0d, 3d, 10d, 500d}
      java.lang.Double[][] getRestrictions()
      This returns all restrictions of the problem.

      example restrictions:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d, 0d},
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 0d},
      {0d, 0d, 1d, 0d}}

      See difference to getCoefficients()!
      java.lang.Double[][] getSimplexTableau()
      Returns a simplex tableau of the current problem.

      example tableau:
      {{1d, 2d, 0d, 0d, 200d}, restriction 1
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 0d, 50d}, restriction 2
      {0d, 0d, 1d, 0d, 80d}, restriction 3
      {0d, 0d, 3d, 10d, 500d}} function
      boolean isSolvableWithBAndB()
      Defines if this problem is solvable with branch and bound algorithm.

      Updates the function of the problem.
